In the documentation we mention that AuthConfig objects are passed in the X-Registry-Auth header, but we never document the format of AuthConfig objects, or when/why they get passed.

If you've done a docker login, you'll get a base64 encoded json file which looks like:

{"username":"pdevine","password":"mysecretpassword","auth":"","email":"pdevine@foo.com","serveraddress":"192.168.1.101"}

If you then do a docker logout, you'll get:

{"auth":"","email":""}

If you're using passed tokens, you'll get something like:

{"registrytoken": "foo"}

We should document:
